title: Merge pull request #7 from djkovrik/master
message:
Merge pull request #7 from djkovrik/master

Add Russian translation

title: - Fixed bug hampering recording on Android 6.0 devices due to non requested storage permission
message:
- Fixed bug hampering recording on Android 6.0 devices due to non requested storage permission
- Raster icons changed by vector icons
- Message updated on ActivityProcesses for Android 7.0+ devices
- API tools bumped from 23 to 25.3
- Spaces changed by tabs
- Copyright message year updated from 2015 to 2017

title: Known issues section removed from the README.md file.
message: Known issues section removed from the README.md file.

message: Added information about CPU and memory data gathering and multi-core devices

title: AndroidProcesses version and copyright year updated.
message: AndroidProcesses version and copyright year updated.

title: Fix for Sony Xperia phones which were not detecting the navigation bar.
message: Fix for Sony Xperia phones which were not detecting the navigation bar.

title: The process list works again for devices with Android 5.1.1+.
message: The process list works again for devices with Android 5.1.1+.

message: Some unused code removed. Some comments added.

title: minSdkVersion changed from 14 to 16 so that the com.android.support library is…
message: minSdkVersion changed from 14 to 16 so that the com.android.support library is not needed anymore. ActivityPreferences not used class removed.

title: targetSdkVersion updated to Android SDK v23 (6.0).
message: targetSdkVersion updated to Android SDK v23 (6.0).

title: I came across with a Vodafone Ultra phone which had the Menu button implemented…
message: I came across with a Vodafone Ultra phone which had the Menu button implemented as an apps Navigation bar button long-click. With the below code and with these rare phones the AnotherMonitor menu button was hidden. Not anymore.

title: I came across with a Vodafone Ultra phone which had the Menu button implemented…
message: I came across with a Vodafone Ultra phone which had the Menu button implemented as an apps Navigation bar button long-click. With the below code and with these rare phones the AnotherMonitor menu button was hidden. Not anymore.

title: ActivityProcesses has been updated to inform the user about the Android 5.1.1…
message: ActivityProcesses has been updated to inform the user about the Android 5.1.1 API change with processes retrieving.

title: Defaults values for the Read, Update and Width intervals are now set from a…
message: Defaults values for the Read, Update and Width intervals are now set from a single same public static final integer.

title: Initial value for C.intervalRead corrected from 500 to 1000. Removed readPrefs() method.
message: Initial value for C.intervalRead corrected from 500 to 1000. Removed readPrefs() method.

title: - Now when an Activity is created it remembers whether on the graphic the memory…
message:
- Now when an Activity is created it remembers whether on the graphic the memory is shown or not and whether the processes list show CPU usage or memory.
- About text rearranged. Lateral margin added to the About text.
- Minor refactoring: removed unnecessary castings.
- Version code and version number updated.

title: Corrected bug which added extra bottom space to the screen to phones that had…
message: Corrected bug which added extra bottom space to the screen to phones that had physical 'Switch apps' button. These phones (like Samsung Galaxy S5) don't need screen bottom space for the Navigation bar because the phone already has this bar integrated.

title: 'IllegalArgumentException: Underflow in restoreToCount' problem on app opening addressed.
message: 'IllegalArgumentException: Underflow in restoreToCount' problem on app opening addressed.

title: 'About' text changed and link to GitHub added.
message: 'About' text changed and link to GitHub added.

title: - Fixed: now when on some Activity on top of ActivityMain the Close button from…
message:
- Fixed: now when on some Activity on top of ActivityMain the Close button from the icons system bar is pressed the whole stack of activities will be close as expected.
- Fixed: on the ActivityProcesses, the OK button will work after the screen is rotated.
- Changed: on the ActivityProcesses, when the OK button is pressed and there are no processes selected a Toast will be shown to the user informing about this.
- Changed: versionCode and versionName updated.
